😍Since I’m not the best at cooking my aunt and mommy helped me out with this very simple but delicious “3 cheese chicken pasta” recipe!!!

The key to enjoying high carb meals without the weight gain is CARB CRUSHER! Take 2 veggie capsules 30 minutes previous to intaking your main meals! They will block the body from storing carbs and fats!

📌Here are the ingredients:

1/2 box of cooked pasta (penne)
4-5 chopped tomatoes
1 spoonful of oil
1 cube chicken flavor
2 shredded chicken breast
1 Nestle cream can
1 spoonful garlic (if wanted)
1 pinch salt
3 pinch sugar
1 bottle 3 cheese: parmesan, asiago, romano

📌Here are the instructions:

Once your pastas are cooked (we did penne), add the 4-5 chopped tomatoes, 1 cube of chicken flavor, 1 spoonful of oil, 3 pinch of sugar, 1 pinch of salt and wait for the tomatoes to dissolve for like 6 minutes. Then add the shredded chicken, the can of cream, and 1 spoonful of garlic if you like. I love garlic! Then last but not least, add the 3 cheeses. You can either add it to the pot or on each serving seperately. We added it seperately so it wouldnt dry.

👇🏼DO YOU DO BULKING VS CUTTING SEASONS??

🚩MY EATING HABITS WHEN I WENT THROUGH A BULKING SEASON:
-
📌PRE WORKOUT MEAL:

Before a good leg day workout, it’s good to eat simple carbohydrates, because they are digested fast and provide quick energy. It’s even better to eat than not to eat in order to burn more during your weight lifting session. Things you could eat: half a sweet potato, a granola bar, oatmeal, Greek yogurt, a rice cake. Before leg day I usually have the sweet potato after taking my #TrimV. -
-
- - 📌POST WORKOUT MEAL
If your main goal is to build and grow muscle, try to eat at least 30 grams of protein and 30 to 35 grams of carbs within about 15 minutes of your workout. .
.
During a workout, your body breaks down muscle glycogen as well as muscle protein structures. Therefore, following exercise, your body needs to replenish its energy stores and repair muscle tissue to allow for new growth. In order to do this, you’ll need to consume enough carbs to promote substantial insulin release. A protein-packed shake and protein snacks are a great way to rebuild tissue that breaks down during exercise. .

🚩MY EATING HABITS NOW WHILE I WANT TO CUT AND STAY TONED: 

If you’re just trying to stay in shape or shed pounds, I will always promote intermittent fasting because it’s what I know and what has worked for me throughout the years. I started fasting with 16 hours, then 19, and now I usually fast from 19-24 hrs. If you want to cut but arent into fasting you can take your time and eat the same amount but within 45 minutes or an hour after your workout. 

Im always in cutting/maintenance season because Im looking to trim, tone and just stay svelte. Thats why I always take Trim-V and keep my midsection toned and tight with Vbelt and Gel-V. I usually have one meal a day, try to eat healthy 80/20 and love HIIT workouts!

Regardless if you’re cutting, bulking, post pregnancy, losing weight, mantaining, make sure you supplement your body and skin with out products. Gel-V is repairative and preventative and will enhance your journey always!

I would love to say this is just a funny reel but I’ve been there once or twiceeeee🙊and if you’re a woman, I’m sure you’ve at some point been there as well! It’s such a difficult situation when you like someone who is emotionally unavailable and they constantly play the “hot and cold” game. In Spanish there’s a saying that says: 

“NI CONTIGO, NI SIN TI”

I love being real and sharing experiences because somehow its like therapy and I know many would feel identified with all these heart to heart situations❤️‍🩹

In the meantime, like they say: “Fake it until you make it” & say u have plans.It’s best to be having “you time”, doing a facemask, reading a book, spending time with someone who really loves you🐶, and working on becoming the best version of yourself inside and outside than always being available for someone who’s not 100% down for you!

My best advice if you’re currently going through this is:

1. Take your time to heal and be real with yourself. No need to pretend that you’re happy when you’re not

2. Do things that make your soul feel good: working out, eating healthy, laughing with a friend, spending time with your kids or dog, tanning in the sun, a hobby, etc. (not drinking and party. This tends to make you feel worse afterwards!)

3. Dinner with a friend. I always love to stay in and cry but honestly forcing myself sometimes to go out has been very helpful!

4. Seek therapy if necessary: I thought this was annoying at first but ive learned so much aboutmyself when it comes from someone else! Make sure you find someone you feel comfortable with!

5. Find an event, a trip, a concert, a party or something to look forward to, to prepare for, to get excited about!

6. Last but definitely not least: Give yourself a lil makeover! Doesnt have to be anything fancy or expensive but honestly seeing a change in yourself will motivate you to see there’s life ahead of this situation! Whether its a haircut, a hair dye, getting your lashes done, a new makeup style, or working on your body goals this will change the focus from “him” to you!

💔I did want to share however my best advice if you’re currently going through a break up because I know how difficult this is:

1. Take your time to heal and be real with yourself. No need to pretend that you’re happy when you’re not

2. Do things that make your soul feel good: working out, eating healthy, laughing with a friend, blasting, singing & dancing to your fav music even if you’re alone; spending time with your family, kids or dog, tanning in the sun, a hobby, etc. (not drinking and party. This tends to make you feel worse afterwards!)

3. Dinner with a friend. I always love to stay in and cry but honestly forcing myself sometimes to go out has been very helpful!

4. Seek therapy if necessary: I thought this was annoying at first but ive learned so much about myself when it comes from someone else! Make sure you find someone you feel comfortable with!

5. Find an event, a trip, a concert, a party or something to look forward to, to prepare for, to get excited about!

6. Last but definitely not least: Give yourself a lil makeover! Doesnt have to be anything fancy or expensive but honestly seeing a change in yourself will motivate you to see there’s life ahead of this situation! Whether its a haircut, a hair dye, getting your lashes done, a new makeup style, or working on your body goals this will change the focus from “him” to you!

When you find activities you love to do, fitness stops being a chore. It actually becomes a healthy competition with yourself. You want more, you want to DO more, you want to BE more, you want to achieve more, you want to BECOME better than you were yesterday. 

🏃🏼‍♀️I lead  a very fast paced life. Between work, my family, my pup, and my social committments lol Im always rushing trying to show up for everyone. 

🕚Dancing has become that 1 hr a week for me where I let go and let loose. I disconnect from my day to day stress and I show up for ME. Its a hobby I enjoy for me. Am I the best? No. Has it been easy for me? No. I lack short term memory. I’m not medically diagnosed with (ADD) but many things that happen to me on the daily lead me to believe I struggle with attention deficit. 

However, I give it my all because I dislike slacking, I dislike giving up on myself, I dislike making mistakes, I dislike being mediocre!

I was here all afternoon, showered, changed outfit and kept going cause I wanted to!

Anyways, I just wanted to inspire you guys to show up for yourselves! We’re constantly giving, giving, giving and forget about ourselves. Hope you find an activity you love and invest atleast one hour a week in it. Where you can put your phone down, ask your husband to take care of the kids and focus on you!

😍While embracing your natural height and maintaining good posture will always be the most authentic way to project confidence and presence, there are always some tips and tricks that can help us a little along the way! And today Im here to shed some light on my favorites🔦😅

📏When it comes to looking taller and more svelte in pictures and videos, the placement and angles of your phone can play a significant role in creating an illusion of height. This is largely due to the principle of perspective.

1️⃣Firstly, the placement of your phone can affect the angle at which the photo or video is captured. Placing your phone slightly below knee level and angling it upwards can elongate your body and make you appear taller. By positioning the camera from a lower point, it creates the impression that the viewer is looking up at you, enhancing your height.

2️⃣Positioning your face closer to the foreground and ensuring there are objects of reference behind you can add depth, further emphasizing the length and width of your face. A vertical phone makes your face look longer for those with round faces. A horizontal phone makes your face look fuller for those with longer faces. 

3️⃣Additionally, the distance between you and the camera can also impact your perceived height. By stepping slightly away from the camera and using the phone’s zoom feature if necessary, you can create more space between your body and the lens. This helps to minimize any distortion and allows for a more accurate representation of your height in the image or video.

4️⃣Furthermore, placing the phone on the floor and turning it downside up while playing with the background and foreground can contribute to the illusion of height. Choosing a background with vertical lines, such as tall buildings or trees, can create a visual comparison that enhances your stature.
